          	<h2>About Our Company</h2>
   	    <img src="images/templatemo_image_04.jpg" alt="image" class="image_wrapper image_fl" />
            <p align="justify"><em>Present product and process information intelligently throughout a food supply chain to support management and customer services.</em></p>
            <p align="justify">Support companies for operations management in food supply chains and provide better service to consumers. The companies include all partners in a supply chain: food suppliers (large farms, processors/manufacturers), logistics services (transportation by shipping, rail, road), ports, retailer distribution centres, supermarket stores. </p>
          	<img src="images/templatemo_image_05.jpg"  alt="image" class="image_wrapper image_fr" />
            <p align="justify">The consumers and companies in whole supply chains will need product supply information (product ID, suppliers, batch, location, time, quality changes, delivery arrangement, environment parameters, etc) for management purposes. The management will be only efficient if the information can be shared by all partners in a supply chain and the partners can collaborating with the information in decision making (forecasting, planning, control, etc). Therefore, web-based system is required to provide consumers and supply chain partners with the access to information about products at all stages of a supply chain.</p>
            <p align="justify">The major purpose to share these data is to help decision making through identifying dynamic product quality status (e.g. impacts of the supply process on a batch or case/pallet of products and estimated shelf-life changes, etc). With the data, managers can plan the product processing and supply differently according to different quality/shelf-life status of the products. Different partners in a supply chain may require different forms of information descriptions and illustrations.</p>
